%S A375077 2,2480,8178,45153,3648841,7979090,101130029,339949252,1019547844,
%T A375077 17609764994,1070858041585,5048891644646,18253129921842,
%U A375077 359503904702190
%N A375077 Smallest k such that Product_{i=0..n} (k-i) divides C(2*k,k).
%C A375077 Minimality of a(8)-a(13) is certified by exhaustive search combined with a provably complete small-prime sieve that guards against theoretical false negatives (checking all primes p < 2n+1 for each candidate). The completeness of this screen follows from the Small Prime Barrier Theorem (formally verified in Lean 4 + Mathlib): any non-governor witness must have governor failures confined to primes below 2n+1. See Dehorty link. - _Justin Dehorty_, Mar 23 2026
%H A375077 Thomas Bloom, <a href="https://www.erdosproblems.com/396">Problem 396</a>, Erdős Problems.
%H A375077 Justin Dehorty, <a href="https://github.com/jdehorty/erdos396">Witness Search for Erdos Problem #396</a> (exhaustive search, validation certificates, and Lean 4 formal proof of the Small Prime Barrier Theorem).
%H A375077 Justin Dehorty, <a href="https://gist.github.com/jdehorty/9805309936a5cd1e773705fa76a44b99">Catalogue of Search Algorithm Optimizations for this sequence</a>.
%H A375077 Erdős problems database contributors, <a href="https://github.com/teorth/erdosproblems/blob/main/README.md#table">Erdős problem database</a>, see no. 396.
%o A375077 (PARI) for(n=1, 20, for(k=n+1,100000, if(binomial(2*k,k)%prod(i=0,n,k-i)==0, print1(k, ", "); break)))
%o A375077 (Python)
%o A375077 from math import prod, comb
%o A375077 def A375077(n):
%o A375077     a, c, k = prod(n+1-i for i in range(n+1)), comb(n+1<<1,n+1), n+1
%o A375077     while c%a:
%o A375077         k += 1
%o A375077         a = a*k//(k-n-1)
%o A375077         c = c*((k<<1)-1<<1)//k
%o A375077     return k # _Chai Wah Wu_, Jul 30 2024
